\title{Migrating Bitnami To Bitnami Legacy}

\taxon{skill}

\tag{}

\meta{description}{This rule book helps you migrate Bitnami Helm charts and container images from the bitnami repository to the bitnamilegacy repository.
 This migration is necessary due to Bitnami's transition, effective August 28th, 2025, where existing images will be moved to the legacy repo}

\subtree{
\title{Bitnami to Bitnami Legacy Migration Rule Book}
\subtree{
\title{1. Overview}
\pre{\startverb
This rule book provides a systematic approach for migrating **Bitnami Helm charts** and **container images** from the `bitnami` repository to the `bitnamilegacy` repository.\ This migration is necessary due to Bitnami's transition effective **August 28th, 2025**, where existing images will be moved to the legacy repository.
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Background}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Effective Date:} August 28th, 2025}
\li{\strong{Impact:} All existing Bitnami container images will be moved from \code{\startverb docker.io/bitnami\stopverb} to \code{\startverb docker.io/bitnamilegacy\stopverb}.}
\li{\strong{Helm Charts:} Will continue to work but require image repository updates.}
\li{\strong{Legacy Repository:} Receives no further updates and should only be used as a \strong{temporary migration step}.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Migration Prerequisites}
\ul{
\li{Access to Kubernetes clusters (staging, sandbox, production).}
\li{Terraform access with appropriate permissions.}
\li{Helm CLI installed and configured.}
\li{kubectl access to target clusters.}
\li{Communication with stakeholders regarding downtime or risks.}
}
}

